         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Clifton Spring, ¶  9/1/84. ¶  ¶ It is with much regret, dear Mr Morrison, ¶  that I hear of your suffering still from recurrent fever, and as I am myself unable to undertake long drives, on account of...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">84.01.09</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To George Morrison</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">Ml MSS.312/36 Morrison papers, vol. 36, p. 5, Mitchell Library, State Library of New South Wales, Sydney.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Clifton Spring,<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Vic.</p>
               </note> 9/1/84.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>It is with much regret, dear Mr Morrison,<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg style="">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>George Ernest Morrison, 1862-1920.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> that I hear of your suffering still from recurrent fever, and as I am myself unable to undertake long drives, on account of the severity of my cough, I cannot venture to see you on your own place. I have however resolved, to remain here for one week longer, and if you should feel meanwhile well enough, I shall be delighted to see you here, when we could fully confer on matters connected with future researches on the Papuan Flora.<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Morrison had recently returned to Melbourne from an exploring expedition to New Guinea during which he had received severe spear wounds that he was lucky to survive.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>With the best wishes for your recovery and every respect, I remain your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Ferd. von Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Should your state of health not permit a tour to this place soon, then — I hope — to see you some day in Melbourne.</p>
         </div>
